# Thoughts Journal System

The user maintains a daily journal at `~/code/thoughts/`. It contains:

- `daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — daily session logs, plans, and notes
- `ideas.md` — persistent idea backlog
- `open-questions.md` — unresolved questions
- `decisions.md` — decision log with rationale
- `til.md` — things learned (canonical for TILs; session-summarize appends here)
- `parking-lot.md` — deferred / out-of-scope items to revisit later
- `weekly/` — weekly retrospective rollups (`YYYY-WNN.md`)
- `projects/` — per-project running notes

At the end of a session the user may ask to summarize and log the session. The `session-summarize` skill handles this. Do not proactively invoke it — wait for the user to ask.
